38 years, encompassing more than 100 missions in 35 counties ranging from debris clearance
39 to humanitarian support; and
40 WHEREAS, the selfless actions of the Georgia Department of Defense and its components
41 at home and abroad in 2024 stands as an example of putting service before self, and it is
42 abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of these remarkable and
43 distinguished Georgians be appropriately recognized.
44 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
45 recognize February 6, 2025, as National Guard Day at the state capitol and commend the
46 men and women of the Georgia National Guard for their strength, leadership, courage, and
47 selfless service.
48 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
49 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
50 press.
